# Pipeline Updates

The project has a local pipeline at `pipeline.md` (root). Update it when:

- The user says "add to the log", "log this", "add to pipeline", "add to upcoming notes", or similar
- The user reports a new bug — add under Open Items with `BUG` OPEN, date, optional [P2], and brief description
- The user shares a plan or idea — add under Open Items with appropriate tag (`FEAT`, `MOD`, `IMPR`, `IDEA`)
- **Only when the user agrees work is complete:** add a Changelog entry and move the item to Closed/Fixed with `BUG` FIXED or `FEAT`/`MOD`/`IMPR` CLOSED — do not auto-close or auto-add to changelog; when you believe work is complete, request confirmation (e.g. "Should I close this and add it to the changelog?") before updating

**Entry format:** `tag` `status` `YYYY-MM-DD` [priority] (module) Title. Optional detail or → plan link.

**Tags:** `BUG` (defects), `FEAT` (new features), `MOD` (module-specific), `IMPR` (improvements/refactors), `IDEA` (backlog/speculative), `DOC` (documentation)

**Status:** `OPEN` (active), `FIXED` (resolved bugs), `CLOSED` (done or dropped)

**Priority** (optional, for OPEN items): `P0` (major), `P1` (minor), `P2` (patch)

**Module** (optional): `Focus`, `Presence`, or omit for core/general. Use parentheses, e.g. `(Focus)`.

**Format conventions:**
- **Changelog:** `YYYY-MM-DD — (module) One-line summary.` or `YYYY-MM-DD — One-line summary.` (newest first); include module when the change is module-specific.
- **Open Items / Closed/Fixed:** Use tag + status + date + optional [priority] + optional (module) + title
- Use `YYYY-MM-DD` for dates. Keep entries one line when possible.

**Pipeline unique code (for chat names):** When working on a pipeline item, use a unique code so the chat is easy to find. Format: `TAG-YYYYMMDD-slug` where slug is a short lowercase hyphenated form of the title (e.g. `FEAT-20260213-quest-header-count`). When starting a chat for a pipeline item, name the chat with this code or include it in the first message.
